==English==
===Etymology===
From [[w:Star Trek|Star Trek]] + [[-ie]]

===Noun===
'''Trekkie''' (''plural'' '''Trekkies''')

#A fan of the [[TV]] [[science fiction]] series ''[[w:Star_Trek|Star Trek]]''.

====Synonyms====
*[[Trekker]]

====Usage note====
*This term is considered derogatory by the fans themselves, who prefer the term ''Trekker''.

====Quotations====
*'''1992''' - ''StarTrek VI is a fast-moving, vigorous book that will not disappoint the legions of Trekkies who avidly follow the adventure of their heroes.'' - Unknown, ''Review of Star Trek - The Undiscovered Country'' in ''Amiga User International'', December 1992, HHL Publishing (UK), page 90.

*'''2002''' - ''I have a major confession to make which will probably incur the wrath of all Trekkies out there.'' - Jessica Mellor, article ''Trek & Treat'', ''The Daily Mirror'' (UK), Saturday, August 10, 2002. p. 44.